post_text:
We remember:

19 years ago, 246 people went to sleep in preparation for their morning flights. 2,606 people went to sleep in preparation for work in the morning tomorrow. 343 firefighters went to sleep in preparation for their morning shift. 60 police officers went to sleep in preparation for morning patrol. 8 paramedics went to sleep in preparation for the morning shift of saving lives. None of them saw past 10:00 am Sept 11, 2001. In one single moment life may never be the same.

As you live and enjoy the breaths you take today and tonight before you go to sleep in preparation for your life tomorrow, kiss the ones you love, snuggle a little tighter, and never take one second of your life for granted.
Never forget. 🇺🇸

Dear Urban Pathways K-5 Families,

Here are just a couple of announcements for the week of July 7th, 2020. If your student still has any personal belongings at the school, they need to be picked up between July 8th and July 10th from 8 AM to 3 PM. We will be using the same process in place with our surrounding school districts. Any personal belongings not picked up by end of day, July 10th, will be donated to local shelters and clothing donation sites in our area.

Our next Parent Feedback Meeting will be held on Wednesday, July 8th at 6:00 PM. Please check out our Facebook page for the link. Be sure you have the Zoom app downloaded on your device.

Join Zoom Meeting
https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83464549007?pwd=Yys4VkYvVUl3eU9FRXB5YkRpUjkrZz09

post_text:
Dear Urban Pathways K-5 Families,

Please mark your calendars for the dates to return all laptops and chargers that were borrowed during the school closure. Our school will be open for families to return these items on June 9th, June 10th, June 11th, and June 12th from 8 AM to 3 PM each day. Please make sure that a family friend or relative returns the laptop within this window of time. Families will be responsible for the cost of any laptops and chargers that are not returned during this time. We will inspect all items for damage upon return as well.

In addition, all families in grades K-5 should visit the school between June 9th and 12th, from 8 AM and 3 PM, to pick up final report cards, yearbooks, and any student belongings that may have been left in desks, lockers, and cubbies before the school closure began. We will have these items collected and ready for families in the cafeteria.

Sincerely,

Urban Pathways K-5 College Charter School

post_text:
Dear Families,

We hope you had a restful Spring Break! Learning across K-5 resumes today. Students in grades 3-5 should be actively logging on to their computers and engaging in Google Classroom learning. As we shared last week, students in grades K-2 will continue to engage in Instructional Packet learning. A new packet with two-week's worth of learning was mailed to all students in K-2 today. Those packets should arrive to families in K-2 within the next couple of days via postal mail so that learning may resume. We appreciate your continued support as we navigate this new way of "going to school" together.

Sincerely,

Urban Pathways K-5 College Charter School

Today's announcement, while not unexpected, is disappointing for many. We kept hoping we'd have even a few days together before the year ended.

We are determined to make the rest of our school year positive and productive. We're all learning so much during this time of remote learning.

So incredibly thankful for the technology that keeps us connected, and for the parents who make it work every day.

We got this! We miss you!

post_text:
We were able to contact them to get a link.

https://internetessentials.com/

Do Your Students Need Internet Access?: We have heard that one of the biggest concerns for our schools looking to provide online continuity of education is ensuring EVERY student has internet access. Comcast is offering their Internet Essentials for free for 2 months. Interested families can use this link to get more information or call 1-855-846-8376. For folks in the Lehigh Valley, RCN is providing 60-day free Lifeline Internet for K-12 students. Interested adults should call 866-926-6704 to receive additional information about eligibility and request this service. PCPCS encourages our members to reach out to your local internet providers to see if they are providing similar offers for your families.

post_text:
Need internet? See below.

Do Your Students Need Internet Access?: We have heard that one of the biggest concerns for our schools looking to provide online continuity of education is ensuring EVERY student has internet access. Comcast is offering their Internet Essentials for free for 2 months. Interested families can call 1-855-846-8376. For folks in the Lehigh Valley, RCN is providing 60-day free Lifeline Internet for K-12 students. Interested adults should call 866-926-6704 to receive additional information about eligibility and request this service. PCPCS encourages our members to reach out to your local internet providers to see if they are providing similar offers for your families.

post_text:
Governor Wolfe has officially declared a state of emergency for all PA schools. Urban Pathways K-5 College Charter School will be closed for two weeks beginning Monday, March 16th through March 27th.

Families will have three days (Monday through Wednesday) from 7-3 to come to the school building to pick up work packets or laptops and chargers. These items are necessary for instruction. If a family in 3-5 DOES NOT need a laptop or charger, they will not need to come in. The students in grades 3-5 will access Google Classroom from the home computer.

Our food service company will also provide lunches to students for the first week out (as a trial) to see if enough students are interested. If so, we will extend beyond the first week. Bagged lunches will be available for families between 11 AM and 12 PM next week.

**video states potential closing, we ARE CLOSED NOW. Please watch the video for details on our plan for online learning and learning packets**

post_text:
A big thank you to the students of UPK6-12, who came to our school Tuesday to help us celebrate Black History month. The UPK6-12 students did monologues, poetry, hip hop dancing, and showed our young UPK5CCS students to begin with the end in mind and to set goals. Thank you UPK6-12 for sharing your talents with us.

Also, FRZY also was there to share this message......

"Had a balllll today with the amazing kids from UPK5CCS! Thank you so much for having me. We talked about a lot of great black history and hip hop. And the suggestions you all gave me to freestyle about where perfect. You guys rock and I’ll sleep great tonight knowing you guys represent the next generation of black history. 👑👑👑👑👑 thank you so much!!!❤️❤️"
~FRZY
February 24, 2020

Follow your dreams and ALWAYS begin with the end in mind!!!!!

post_text:
We are leaders building pathways for success. Our mission is to help every child find a pathway to a successful adult life in the city and beyond.

Knowing your destination is crucial for success. At Urban Pathways K-5, we encourage all of our young scholars to plan for college. Each day we model this with our expectations, coursework and goal setting. As one of the many initiatives to support this college-bound environment, we wear HBCU shirts each and every Friday.

post_text: Saturday tutoring is off to a great start. Our program is more than just tutoring. It is an amazing opportunity for the amazing students from Shady Side Academy to mentor our amazing students from UPK5CCS. Today we got to see mentoring, smiles, laughter, learning, and relationships being built.

post_text:
Today was our First Friday celebration. Each class gets to do their chant for their HBCU, we pick one of the four principles: be kind, be respectful, be responsible, and be safe. We focused on the principle being kind today.
We ended our First Friday celebration by dancing! The students were challenged by Ms. Potter to make an effort to be more kind. The challenge was accepted!
